article.headline: Monmouth, N.J. 49, Sacred Heart 8
article.story: FAIRFIELD, Conn. (AP) -- David Sinisi tallied 200 yards and three rushing touchdowns as Monmouth won a 49-8 victory over Sacred Heart on Saturday. The defense for Sacred Heart (2-4, 0-2) allowed the most points to an NEC team in the school's history. Sinisi broke free for a 41-yard run in the first quarter and a 99-yard scoring strike with 1:52 left in the first half, giving Monmouth (1-4, 1-1) a 35-2 lead. Ayo Falae scored on a 14-yard blocked punt return just 1:48 into the game, and the Pioneers' only rebuttal in the half was a team safety in the second. Jason Payne ran for 123 yards and Brian Friedman converted on a 4-yard run in the fourth, but the Pioneers struggled on offense elsewhere. Quarterback Tyler McKeon was 13-of-24 for 85 yards. His counterpart, Brett Burke, threw 241 yards on 15-of-19 passing while throwing two touchdowns for the Hawks. Monmouth recorded 593 yards of total offense and allowed 274 to Sacred Heart.
